---
export const prerender = true;
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
const lastUpdated = "19 February 2026";
---

<BaseLayout
    title="Privacy Policy"
    description="Privacy Policy of Swift Support Solutions - how we collect, use, store, and protect your personal data in compliance with Nepal's Electronic Transactions Act 2063."
>
    <section class="bg-slate-900 text-white">
        <div class="container py-12">
            <div class="max-w-2xl">
                <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
                <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm">
                    Last updated: {lastUpdated}
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-16 bg-white">
        <div class="container">
            <div
                class="max-w-3xl prose prose-slate prose-sm mx-auto"
                style="line-height:1.8; color:#334155;"
            >
                <div
                    class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-xl p-5 mb-8 text-sm text-amber-800"
                >
                    <strong>Legal Basis:</strong> This Privacy Policy is issued in
                    compliance with the <strong
                        >Electronic Transactions Act 2063 (2006)</strong
                    > of Nepal and aligns with internationally recognised personal
                    data protection principles. By using our services, you acknowledge
                    this Policy.
                </div>

                <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-3">
                    1. Who We Are
                </h2>
                <p>
                    Swift Support Solutions Pvt. Ltd. ("we", "our", "the
                    Company") is a professional business consulting firm
                    registered under the <strong>Companies Act 2063</strong> of Nepal,
                    operating from Kathmandu, Bagmati Province, Nepal. We provide
                    business consultation, financial advisory, accounting, tax and
                    VAT support, events management, marketing, fundraising, project
                    management, and business development services.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-3">
                    2. Information We Collect
                </h2>
                <p>
                    We may collect the following categories of personal
                    information:
                </p>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-sm">
                    <li>
                        <strong>Identity data:</strong> Full name, designation, company
                        name
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Contact data:</strong> Email address, phone number,
                        postal address
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Financial data:</strong> PAN/VAT number, bank details
                        (only where required for service delivery)
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Business data:</strong> Company registration number,
                        business type, industry sector
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Technical data:</strong> IP address, browser type,
                        pages visited, cookies (analytics only)
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Communications:</strong> Correspondence you send us
                        via contact forms, email, or phone
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    We do not collect sensitive personal data (e.g. health,
                    biometric, or political data) unless strictly required and
                    with your explicit consent.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-3">
                    3. How We Use Your Information
                </h2>
                <p>We use your personal data to:</p>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-sm">
                    <li>
                        Provide and manage the business services you have
                        engaged us for
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Comply with our obligations under Nepal tax,
                        registration, and regulatory authorities (IRD, OCR, NRB)
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Respond to your enquiries and schedule consultations
                    </li>
                    <li>Send service-related communications and updates</li>
                    <li>
                        Improve our website and service delivery (using
                        anonymised analytics)
                    </li>
                    <li>Meet our legal and contractual obligations</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    We do <strong>not</strong> sell, rent, or trade your personal
                    information to third parties for marketing purposes.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-3">
                    4. Legal Basis for Processing
                </h2>
                <p>
                    Under Nepal's <strong
                        >Electronic Transactions Act 2063</strong
                    > and applicable contract law, we process your personal data on
                    the following bases:
                </p>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-sm">
                    <li>
                        <strong>Contract performance:</strong> To fulfil our service
                        agreement with you
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Legal obligation:</strong> To comply with IRD, OCR,
                        and other statutory requirements
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Legitimate interests:</strong> To operate, improve,
                        and secure our services
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Consent:</strong> For optional communications such
                        as newsletters
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-3">
                    5. Data Sharing
                </h2>
                <p>We may share your data with:</p>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-sm">
                    <li>
                        <strong>Nepal government authorities:</strong> IRD, OCR, NRB,
                        and other regulators as legally required
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Service providers:</strong> Trusted third-party software
                        and infrastructure providers under strict confidentiality
                        agreements
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Professional advisors:</strong> Auditors and legal
                        counsel, where necessary
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    All third parties are required to handle your data securely
                    and in compliance with applicable law.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-3">
                    6. Data Retention
                </h2>
                <p>
                    We retain personal data for as long as necessary to provide
                    services and meet legal obligations. Financial and tax
                    records are retained for a minimum of <strong
                        >5 years</strong
                    > in accordance with the Income Tax Act 2058 and VAT Act 2052.
                    After this period, data is securely deleted or anonymised.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-3">
                    7. Cookies
                </h2>
                <p>
                    Our website uses essential cookies for functionality and
                    optional analytics cookies (e.g. Google Analytics) to
                    understand usage patterns. You may disable non-essential
                    cookies in your browser settings without affecting core
                    functionality.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-3">
                    8. Your Rights
                </h2>
                <p>You have the right to:</p>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-sm">
                    <li>Access the personal data we hold about you</li>
                    <li>Request correction of inaccurate or incomplete data</li>
                    <li>
                        Request deletion of your data (subject to legal
                        retention obligations)
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Withdraw consent for optional communications at any time
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Lodge a complaint with the relevant authority if you
                        believe your data has been mishandled
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at <a
                        href="mailto:privacy@swiftsupportsolutions.com.np"
                        class="text-amber-600 hover:underline"
                        >privacy@swiftsupportsolutions.com.np</a
                    >.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-3">
                    9. Data Security
                </h2>
                <p>
                    We implement appropriate technical and organisational
                    measures to protect your information from unauthorised
                    access, disclosure, alteration, or loss. This includes
                    encrypted data transmission (HTTPS), access controls, and
                    regular security reviews.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-3">
                    10. Changes to This Policy
                </h2>
                <p>
                    We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. Significant
                    changes will be communicated via email or a prominent notice
                    on our website. The "Last updated" date at the top reflects
                    the most recent revision.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-3">
                    11. Contact Us
                </h2>
                <p>For any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy:</p>
                <div
                    class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 text-sm border border-slate-100"
                >
                    <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900">
                        Swift Support Solutions Pvt. Ltd.
                    </p>
                    <p>Kathmandu, Bagmati Province, Nepal</p>
                    <p>
                        Email: <a
                            href="mailto:privacy@swiftsupportsolutions.com.np"
                            class="text-amber-600 hover:underline"
                            >privacy@swiftsupportsolutions.com.np</a
                        >
                    </p>
                    <p>Registered under Companies Act 2063, Nepal</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</BaseLayout>
